obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `THE ADMINISTRATORS-GENERAL ACT, 1963`
  line _______
  line `ARRANGEMENT OF SECTIONS`
  line ________
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement.`
  line `2. Definitions.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `T HE O FFICE OF THE A DMINISTRATOR- G ENERAL`
  line `3. Appointment of Administrator-General.`
  line `4. Appointment and powers of Deputy Administrator-General.`
  line `5. Incorporation.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `R IGHTS, P OWERS AND D UTIES OF THE A DMINISTRATOR- G ENERAL`
  line `( a ) Grant of letters of administration and probate`
  line `6. Jurisdiction of High Court for the whole State.`
  line `7. Administrator-General entitled to letters of administration, unless granted to next-of-kin.`
  line `8. Administrator-General, entitled to letters of administration in preference to creditors, certain`
  line `legatees or friends.`
  line `9. Right of Administrator-General to apply for administration of estates.`
  line `10. Power of Administrator-General to collect and hold assets where immediate action is required.`
  line `11. Grant of probate or letters of administration to person appearing in the course of proceedings`
  line `taken by Administrator-General.`
  line `12. Grant of administration to Administrator-General in certain cases.`
  line `13. Administrator-General not precluded from applying for letters within one month after death.`
  line `( b ) Revocation of grants`
  line `14. Recall of Administrator-General ’ s administration and grant of probate, etc., to executor or`
  line next-of-kin.
  line `15. Cost of obtaining administration, etc., may, on revocation, be ordered to be paid to`
  line `Administrator-General out of estate.`
  line `16. After revocation letters granted to Administrator-General to be deemed, as to him, to have been`
  line `voidable only.`
  line `17. Payments made by Administrator-General prior to revocation.`
  line `( c ) General`
  line `18. Administrator-General ’ s petition for grant of letters of administration.`
  line `19. Name in which probate or letters to be granted.`
  line `20. Effect of probate or letters granted to Administrator-General.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
