obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `21. [ Omitted. ]`
  line `22. Transfer by private executor or administrator of interest under probate or letters.`
  line `23. Distribution of assets.`
  line `24. Appointment of Official Trustee as trustee of assets after completion of administration.`
  line `25. Power of High Court to give directions regarding administration of estate.`
  line `26. No security to be required from Administrator-General.`
  line `27. Manner in which petition to be verified by Administrator-General.`
  line `28. Entry of Administrator-General not to constitute notice of a trust.`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `G RANT OF C ERTIFICATE`
  line `29. In what cases Administrator-General may grant certificate.`
  line `30. Grant of certificate to creditors and power to take charge of certain estates.`
  line `31. Administrator- General not bound to grant certificate unless satisfied of claimant’s title, etc.`
  line `32. Effect of certificate.`
  line `33. Revocation of certificate.`
  line `34. Surrender of revoked certificate.`
  line `35. Payment to holder of certificate before it is revoked.`
  line `36. Administrator-General not bound to take out administration on account of assets for which he has`
  line `granted certificate.`
  line `37. Transfer of certain assets to executor or administrator in country of domicile for distribution.`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `L IABILITY`
  line `38. Liability of Government.`
  line `39. Creditor’s suit against Administrator -General.`
  line `40. Notice of suit not required in certain cases.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `F EES`
  line `41. Fees.`
  line `42. Disposal of fees.`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `A UDIT OF THE A DMINISTRATOR- G ENERAL’S A CCOUNTS`
  line `43. Audit.`
  line `44. Auditors to examine accounts and report to Government.`
  line `45. Power of auditors to summon and examine witnesses, and to call for documents.`
  line `46. Costs of audit, etc.`
