obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `CHAPTER VIII`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `47. General powers of administration.`
  line `48. Power to summon and examine witnesses.`
  line `49. Power of person beneficially interested to inspect Administrator- General’s account, etc., and take`
  line copies.
  line `50. False evidence.`
  line `51. Assets unclaimed for twelve years to be transferred to Government.`
  line `52. Mode of proceeding by claimant to recover principal money so transferred.`
  line `53. Succession Act or Companies Act not to affect Administrator-General.`
  line `54. Savings of provisions of Police Acts for presidency-towns.`
  line `55. Order of court to be equivalent to decree.`
  line `56. Provision for administration by Consular Officer in case of death in certain circumstances of`
  line `foreign subject.`
  line `57. Letters of administration not necessary in respects of small estates administered by`
  line `Administrator-General in accordance with certain Acts.`
  line `58. Powers to grant Administrator-General letters limited for purpose of dealing with assets in`
  line `accordance with the Army and Air Force (Disposal of Private Property) Act, 1950, or the Navy`
  line `Act, 1957.`
  line `59. Act not to affect Army and Air Force (Disposal of Private Property) Act, 1950, or the Navy`
  line `Act, 1957.`
  line `60. Saving of provisions of Indian Registration Act, 1908.`
  line `61. Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  line `62. Power of State Government to make rules.`
  line `63. Laying of rules made by Central Government before Parliament.`
  line `64. Repeal and savings.`
